                            <lb/>
                        
                        JOHN SHERMAN HOYT
                            <lb/>
                        ELLERY S. JAMES
                            <lb/>
                        FRANKLIN B. KIRKBRIDGE
                    </hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 18, 1929</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                    <note type="curatorial">[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]</note>
                </opener>
                <p>It is such a pleasure to enclose a statement in regard to your reading. You certainly left a delightful impression with your friends in New York City. So many have spoken of you and wish that you might live here. Perhaps your change of plans, and as I understand it, possibly business relationships, may bring you to us permanently with all the Neihardt family. If so, do consider living at Chirstodora House.</p>
                
                <p>What a joy it would be to have you, and how our boys would gather around you to hear you tell stories and read poetry to them in the firelight, or by our camp fire out at Northover!</p>
                
                <p>You will be interested to know that the work of our Poet's Guild is developing in rather an amazing way. Our editorial committee is going to meet once a month at a "dutch treat" luncheon in the big upstairs dining room. They are now conferring with the Ease<sic>East</sic> Side Chamber of Commerce in regard to our poetry festivals, and the East Side Chamber of Commerce is going to contribute a poem to the "Unbound Anthology".</p>
                
                <p>We need your advise<sic>advice</sic> and adventure and your wonderful gift for pioneering which makes your poetry such a living thing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes to Mrs. Neihardt, I am</salute>
                
                    <salute>Cordially yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Anna Hempstead Branch</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
